						<summary>

						<p>Records gift of money and 1 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land in the village Pēyāṭṭi in Kulaśēkharaśaruppēdimaṅgalam by Kēśuvaṉ Sundarattōḷuḍaiyāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Piḷḷai Śiṅgapperumāḷ Kūttaṉ for offerings to the goddess in his name on his birthday every year. The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">36th year</hi> of the king's reign.</p>						

						</summary>
